1
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:51,200
LU'S SHOP

2
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:10,280
LU'S SHOP

3
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:16,640
You're Mr. Lu, right?

4
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:18,320
Yes.

5
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:31,000
This pair of shoes… I've seen them.

6
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:34,800
Did someone ask you
to make these this summer?

7
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:36,120
Who was that person?

8
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:37,640
No idea.

9
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:40,640
My dad took that job.

10
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:43,280
He's out of town getting materials.
Maybe in two days?

11
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:55,040
Two days later,
that young officer showed up on time.

12
00:02:55,640 --> 00:02:56,520
He met my dad.

13
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:06,760
That's right.

14
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:10,360
Half a year ago, a young guy came to me.

15
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:13,560
He insisted I turn
a perfectly good pair of red heels

16
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:15,360
into blue ones.

17
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:18,280
It just felt off,
so I didn't want the job.

18
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:21,680
But then he offered me 800 yuan.

19
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:23,360
Eight hundred yuan

20
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:25,800
could buy several pairs
of brand-name shoes.

21
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:29,240
A real pair of shoes,
he wanted it turned fake.

22
00:03:29,320 --> 00:03:31,480
What was he after?

23
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:34,480
What did he look like? Do you remember?

24
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:38,720
A guy in his thirties.

25
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:39,920
Wearing sunglasses.

26
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,400
His face… I didn't see clearly.

27
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:44,520
How tall?

28
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:46,440
His height…

29
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:49,520
You, stand up.

30
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:54,160
About my son's height.

31
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,600
Around 175 cm.

32
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:57,000
Short haircut.

33
00:03:57,080 --> 00:03:58,800
When he spoke, his voice was hoarse.

34
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:01,520
He had three burn marks on his arm.

35
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:03,840
Burn marks?

36
00:04:03,920 --> 00:04:05,760
Scars from being burned with cigarettes.

37
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:14,280
RAN FANGXU'S PATH

38
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,720
BLUE LEATHER HEELS, LILI

39
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:17,440
DU MINGLIANG'S MOTHER, SHOE SELLER
LIU GUIFANG

40
00:04:17,519 --> 00:04:22,280
SHOEMAKER MR. LU
MAN WITH THREE BURN SCARS

41
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:26,120
This man is key to solving
the Yuanlongli June 30th case.

42
00:04:26,840 --> 00:04:29,040
Very likely, he's the real killer.

43
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,480
Same plan as always.

44
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:32,680
We cover both ends.

45
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:35,120
I'll stay in Yuanlongli.

46
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:37,720
You go to the branch
and check local stations.

47
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:40,600
Try to find any useful leads.

48
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:42,320
This is like finding a needle
in a haystack.

49
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:45,920
If we had fingerprints,
I could search the database.

50
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,520
But those burn scars,
how do I even ask about that?

51
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:54,080
I think Uncle Ran went through
the same thing back then.

52
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:57,480
Otherwise, he would've caught
that guy already.

53
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,720
Just… think it through again.

54
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:04,600
If you were Uncle Ran,
where would you go next?

55
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:07,640
RAN FANGXU'S PATH

56
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:23,120
Han, it's me.

57
00:05:23,640 --> 00:05:24,480
Um…

58
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:29,040
Hang on! Let me tell you in a second!

59
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:48,440
My eyes are going blurry.

60
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:51,720
No idea which idiot came up with this
just to mess with me.

61
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:56,720
Uncle Ran,

62
00:05:57,760 --> 00:06:00,320
looking at all that stuff,
doesn't it annoy you?

63
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:01,800
Of course.

64
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:04,360
It's worse when you can't find clues.

65
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:09,800
But I have a theory
that helps solve tough problems.

66
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:10,680
Tell me!

67
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:17,520
Look, when you're solving a problem,

68
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,120
it's like untangling a ball of thread.

69
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:21,160
You have to look closely

70
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:22,840
and find the loose end.

71
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,200
Once you find it, just pull,

72
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:30,680
and the whole thing unravels.

73
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:34,200
Right now, I'm looking for that end.

74
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:40,280
The wind blew it away.

75
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:42,160
Now it's even harder to find.

76
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:44,720
That's weird. Why is it so windy today?

77
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:51,440
Thanks.

78
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,840
PHYSICAL EVIDENCE PHOTOS

79
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:24,840
LIST OF EVIDENCE

80
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:29,040
The key to this case… What is it?

81
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:31,840
‪WHERE DID YOU HIDE THEM?

82
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:33,000
‪I DIDN'T HIDE THEM. SIR, DID YOU CATCH ME
‪BECAUSE SOMETHING HAPPENED TO MENGMENG?

83
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:37,480
Why so dumb?

84
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:41,400
Who are you calling dumb?

85
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:45,520
Me.

86
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,520
There's been a loose thread here.

87
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:49,440
How did I miss it?

88
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:51,000
Q: DID YOU EVER GIFT XU MENG CLOTHING?
A: YES.

89
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:54,880
Xiaohe, pass me the tape.

90
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:15,560
PUBLIC SECURITY

91
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:18,960
WEIYANG PUBLIC SECURITY
BUREAU NANSHAN BRANCH ARCHIVE ROOM

92
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:29,200
CRIMINAL INVESTIGATION FILES

93
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:34,679
CRIMINAL INVESTIGATION FILES

94
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,920
Q: DID YOU EVER GIFT XU MENG CLOTHING?
A: YES.

95
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,400
Q: ANY BOWLS DRESS?

96
00:08:58,480 --> 00:09:00,280
A: I MIGHT. I BOUGHT 11 DRESSES
ALL COME WITH DRY CLEANING GIFT CARD

97
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:03,120
When we interrogated Sun Zhengyong,
I was there too.

98
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:05,800
Sun Zhengyong had an alibi.

99
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:08,280
<i>Qu Dahai can also testify for him.</i>

100
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:10,280
<i>He's not related</i>
<i>to the Yuanlongli June 30th case.</i>

101
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:14,640
And the Bowls dress
mentioned in the statement,

102
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:18,120
Xiao Ran already checked the store's
sales records back then.

103
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,520
Everything matched.

104
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,800
<i>Are you sure</i>
<i>this is the loose thread he meant?</i>

105
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:24,400
I saw Uncle Ran place the tape myself.

106
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:26,920
Dad, try to think carefully again.

107
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:29,160
<i>Back then, did Uncle Ran ever mention</i>

108
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:32,120
<i>the Bowls dress or Sun Zhengyong?</i>

109
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:46,560
We're back.

110
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:50,600
BLESSING

111
00:09:53,640 --> 00:09:55,880
You didn't cause Uncle Ran
any trouble, right?

112
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:57,600
Xiaohe was very well-behaved today.

113
00:09:58,120 --> 00:10:02,040
She even did great
and caught up on all her missed work.

114
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:04,600
That's all thanks to Uncle Ran.
He taught me well.

115
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:05,680
Unlike some people,

116
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:06,920
ask them anything,

117
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,920
they know nothing,
and just shake their head.

118
00:10:09,640 --> 00:10:11,880
Are you taking a jab at me?

119
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:15,160
I get a question right sometimes, okay?

120
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:17,120
If teachers taught like Uncle Ran,

121
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,840
using that detective mindset,

122
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:20,120
I would've graduated early.

123
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:25,000
You, are you trying to graduate early
to go to Beijing for rock music?

124
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:27,000
I could even become a cop on the side.

125
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:30,080
What, on the side?

126
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:32,480
You, put in the same effort
you use for rock music,

127
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:35,480
you still wouldn't match
even half of your Uncle Ran's skills.

128
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:36,960
Uncle Ran isn't a superhero.

129
00:10:37,040 --> 00:10:38,480
He can't even read sheet music.

130
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:41,480
How about this?

131
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:43,000
You teach me music notation,

132
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,200
and I teach you criminal investigation.

133
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:46,040
We learn from each other.

134
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:47,240
Then who's the teacher?

135
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:48,960
We both are.

136
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:51,160
Deal.

137
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:53,400
Deal.

138
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:54,400
Rock on.

139
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,040
And even threw up a rock sign?

140
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:58,840
Hurry and go wash some fruit
for your teacher.

141
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:07,840
Sir, your package.

142
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,560
QI YUANSHAN

143
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:15,320
This is the Mount Wu accident file.

144
00:11:15,920 --> 00:11:17,120
We don't need it now.

145
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,160
Perfect timing.

146
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:20,320
I just wrote something.
Take a look for me.

147
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:26,160
DEADLY BUILDING CASE
YUANLONGLI JUNE 30TH MEMOIR

148
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:28,640
This title, it's catchy.

149
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:32,240
If this gets published,
the title alone will sell it out.

150
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:35,000
Titles are just for show.

151
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:36,320
I care more about the content.

152
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:42,800
ON THE DAY OF JUNE 30TH, 1997…

153
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:49,400
<i>Times change. Energy's limited.</i>
<i>Focus on the big stuff.</i>

154
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,560
Start with clothes and food.

155
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:53,920
I get the first three lines.

156
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,920
What does the last one mean?

157
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,200
It's simple.

158
00:11:57,880 --> 00:11:59,400
What can't we live without?

159
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:01,400
Eating, drinking, and daily needs.

160
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:03,480
Those things leave clues most easily.

161
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:06,760
Sir.

162
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:09,120
That's a great rule.

163
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,520
Why cross it out?

164
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:13,640
Those were just silly rhymes I made up.

165
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:14,800
So much for being a top student.

166
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:17,400
A few words from me fooled you
into calling me "Sir".

167
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,560
Actually, the Yuanlongli June 30th case

168
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:25,640
has two clothing-related clues.

169
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:28,120
One is the blue heels.

170
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:31,360
The other is the Bowls dress.

171
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:34,200
Right, sir.

172
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:37,000
Did you write
the Sun Zhengyong interrogation part?

173
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:39,400
Not yet.

174
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:40,880
I'm only at Song Qingsong.

175
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:42,680
Sun Zhengyong, like Song Qingsong,

176
00:12:42,760 --> 00:12:44,480
later ran off
because of illegal fundraising

177
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:45,560
and debt evasion.

178
00:12:46,520 --> 00:12:49,120
Are you also handling financial cases now?

179
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:51,520
How did you get to Sun Zhengyong?

180
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:57,560
Ran did mention Sun Zhengyong to me.

181
00:12:58,520 --> 00:12:59,840
Back then, Uncle Ran

182
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:01,760
was holding a photo
before he mentioned the loose thread.

183
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:06,720
<i>But what exactly was in the photo,</i>
<i>I don't know.</i>

184
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:08,920
A photo.

185
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:10,920
The loose thread.

186
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:13,720
Sun Zhengyong.

187
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:20,360
RAN FANGXU'S PATH

188
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:23,440
Could it be the dress from Xu Meng's home?

189
00:13:24,040 --> 00:13:25,520
<i>Check it now.</i>

190
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:28,200
<i>There should be a photo</i>
<i>of a dress in the files.</i>

191
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:29,840
<i>It's a Bowls dress.</i>

192
00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:32,800
I've gone through
these two boxes a hundred times.

193
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,760
There's no photo of a Bowls dress.

194
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:37,840
Could it have been borrowed by Uncle Ran,

195
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:39,640
<i>like those blue heels?</i>

196
00:13:40,960 --> 00:13:43,960
Ran must have compared the photo

197
00:13:44,680 --> 00:13:46,480
and found a problem in the statement.

198
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:48,760
<i>Go there now. Go to the Bowls store.</i>

199
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:51,360
Check Sun Zhengyong's purchase records.

200
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:00,800
Hello.

201
00:14:00,880 --> 00:14:01,960
Hello.

202
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:04,800
From Nanshan Branch.
I'm here to ask about something.

203
00:14:05,320 --> 00:14:06,720
Ask away, Officer.

204
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:10,840
You're Jessica too?

205
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:12,680
When I came five years ago,

206
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:14,560
there was a male staff member
with the same name.

207
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:17,240
Here, we change staff, not names.

208
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:20,480
I wanted to ask.

209
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:25,520
In 1997, did buying this dress
come with a dry-cleaning card?

210
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:26,440
Yes.

211
00:14:26,520 --> 00:14:28,440
Not every style did.

212
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:30,520
But this one is a Bowls classic.

213
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:32,360
No matter what year you bought it,
it came with one.

214
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:34,800
And it was a Bowls dry-cleaning card.

215
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,240
Is this it?

216
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:39,040
That's right. That's the one.

217
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:43,280
Can you use this card
to find out who bought the dress?

218
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:45,680
I'm afraid not.

219
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:47,680
The dry-cleaning cards aren't numbered.

220
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:51,440
One moment.

221
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:56,560
This dress was once
brought in for dry cleaning.

222
00:14:56,640 --> 00:14:59,520
Look. Here. There's a check mark.

223
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:02,320
If it was dry-cleaned,

224
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:03,880
we can find the record.

225
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:05,800
I can pull up all the dry-cleaning records

226
00:15:05,880 --> 00:15:08,120
for this dress from 1997.

227
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:10,120
Dry-cleaning records
are linked to sales records.

228
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:12,400
- Thank you so much.
- You're welcome.

229
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,200
- Hello.
- Hello.

230
00:15:17,280 --> 00:15:18,520
Excuse me. How can I help you?

231
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:20,840
I wanted to ask. This store,
how long has it been open?

232
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:23,600
Our store is the Weiyang flagship store.

233
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:24,680
It's been open for over 20 years.

234
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:30,600
Then back in 2003,
did you see this person?

235
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:31,800
2003?

236
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:33,440
I was still in high school then.

237
00:15:36,960 --> 00:15:40,520
So, do you have sales records
for the 1997 classic dress?

238
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:43,200
I'm sorry. Those are internal documents.

239
00:15:43,280 --> 00:15:44,480
We can't just show them.

240
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:46,760
Police investigation.

241
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:48,520
It's not that I won't help.

242
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:51,600
Our store's sales records
are kept for five years at most.

243
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:54,080
Back in 1997, they were still paper files.

244
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:55,440
They were destroyed long ago.

245
00:15:57,640 --> 00:15:59,760
But the provincial headquarters
has an archive room.

246
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:02,080
They should have digital backups.
You can ask there.

247
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:04,920
Provincial headquarters.

248
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,120
Thank you.

249
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:09,640
Officer, I'm sorry.

250
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:11,680
The 1997 records have all been archived.

251
00:16:11,760 --> 00:16:13,120
We need to apply to headquarters.

252
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:15,120
It'll take about two or three days.

253
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:18,320
Thanks, that'd be great.

254
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:19,760
- I'll come back in two days.
- Okay.

255
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:22,160
HUOFENG INSURANCE

256
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:45,200
Qiao.

257
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:53,320
Ran, why did you ask me
to dinner so suddenly?

258
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:54,440
I wasn't even

259
00:16:55,520 --> 00:16:56,480
prepared.

260
00:16:57,520 --> 00:16:59,080
Why prepare for dinner?

261
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:00,960
What do you want?

262
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:03,640
Just some rice noodles is fine.

263
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:09,000
You ordered braised ribs,
sweet-and-sour fish,

264
00:17:09,079 --> 00:17:12,040
boiled beef, and boiled shrimp,
mushrooms with greens, and egg soup.

265
00:17:12,119 --> 00:17:13,839
Six dishes total.
Would you like anything else?

266
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:15,400
The shrimp,

267
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:17,400
maybe skip it.

268
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:18,520
That's all for now.

269
00:17:18,599 --> 00:17:21,079
- Please serve it quickly.
- Sure.

270
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:25,800
You ordered too much.
It's expensive and wasteful.

271
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:28,640
It's fine. We can take leftovers home.

272
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:38,880
FILE

273
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:43,920
I pulled this from the evidence room.

274
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:46,480
After thinking it over,

275
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:50,000
it's best to leave it with you.

276
00:18:00,560 --> 00:18:02,360
Don't open it yet.

277
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:07,160
Then, when you tell me to open it,

278
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:09,320
I'll open it then.

279
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:17,840
FILE

280
00:18:27,760 --> 00:18:29,000
What's wrong?

281
00:18:29,080 --> 00:18:32,080
On New Year's Eve, what are your plans?

282
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:34,280
Are you going home?

283
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:39,640
I don't even have family anymore.

284
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:41,320
What home is there to go back to?

285
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:43,480
I'm sorry.

286
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:48,760
All these years,
I've hated two holidays most.

287
00:18:49,960 --> 00:18:51,520
One is Mid-Autumn Festival,

288
00:18:52,360 --> 00:18:53,800
the other is New Year.

289
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:08,360
Qiao.

290
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:12,360
I'm actually

291
00:19:13,560 --> 00:19:18,040
here today to see you
because Sir asked me to.

292
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:25,200
On New Year's Eve,
he wants to invite you over for dinner.

293
00:19:26,680 --> 00:19:28,400
I'm an outsider. It wouldn't be right.

294
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:29,720
You guys go ahead and celebrate.

295
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,720
Sir's exact words were,

296
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:36,680
"Family should have
a reunion dinner together."

297
00:19:57,840 --> 00:19:59,520
If it doesn't work for you,

298
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:01,080
I I can tell him

299
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:02,520
- you're going out of town.
- It works for me!

300
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:06,960
It really is.

301
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:12,840
But on New Year's Eve,
I promised to take a part-time job.

302
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:14,200
I might be a little late.

303
00:20:14,720 --> 00:20:16,040
But not too late.

304
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:19,280
I will come as soon as I'm done.

305
00:20:21,960 --> 00:20:22,840
It's okay.

306
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:24,920
I'll pick you up then.

307
00:20:49,560 --> 00:20:51,000
BOWLS DRESS

308
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:56,920
Kiddo,

309
00:20:57,880 --> 00:20:59,920
do you ever get this feeling?

310
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:04,600
I keep feeling that this Bowls lead,
just like the blue heels,

311
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:08,080
is a dead end. It goes nowhere.

312
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:09,000
MAN WITH THREE BURN SCARS

313
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:13,800
Yuanlongli's demolition is two weeks away.

314
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:15,720
We need to hurry.

315
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:18,560
Run the Tremaux algorithm
a few more times.

316
00:21:18,640 --> 00:21:19,640
Again?

317
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:22,280
You keep running it
on the same few places.

318
00:21:22,880 --> 00:21:23,840
You're just going in circles.

319
00:21:24,680 --> 00:21:26,840
You might as well go to
the provincial capital with me tomorrow.

320
00:21:27,440 --> 00:21:30,400
Whether Bowls is a dead end,
we won't know until we go.

321
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:36,280
Who messed with this?

322
00:21:36,360 --> 00:21:37,840
Who pulls something like this at night?

323
00:21:37,920 --> 00:21:40,160
Stay away from the window.

324
00:21:48,480 --> 00:21:50,480
Quick, go. Inside, inside.

325
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:07,120
HOLDOUTS GROUP MESSAGE

326
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:16,560
Who smashed my window? Was it Qian Dajun?

327
00:22:16,640 --> 00:22:17,480
Get out here!

328
00:22:17,560 --> 00:22:19,200
Is someone going crazy out there?

329
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:23,560
DU MINGLIANG'S MOTHER
SHOE SELLER, LIU GUIFANG

330
00:22:42,920 --> 00:22:44,680
That Qian Dajun.

331
00:22:44,760 --> 00:22:47,880
Today he smashed a window,
tomorrow he'll break down the door.

332
00:22:49,680 --> 00:22:50,920
I can't go to the provincial capital.

333
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,080
Someone has to stay home.

334
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:53,760
You go and come back fast tomorrow.

335
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:56,200
Dad, then promise me.

336
00:22:56,280 --> 00:22:57,760
No matter what happens,

337
00:22:57,840 --> 00:22:59,120
don't get physical.

338
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:00,560
Call the police if you have to.

339
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:05,080
With what little they can do,
why would I need the police?

340
00:23:06,960 --> 00:23:08,120
Dad.

341
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:18,040
Fine. I promise.

342
00:23:18,120 --> 00:23:19,880
If I can argue, I won't fight.

343
00:23:20,560 --> 00:23:21,440
Promise me.

344
00:23:23,040 --> 00:23:24,920
I promise. I promise.

345
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:31,120
Just don't bother with it today.
Get some sleep.

346
00:23:32,040 --> 00:23:33,920
When I'm back tomorrow, I'll help you.

347
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:42,360
Be careful going downstairs.

348
00:24:00,760 --> 00:24:02,880
MAN WITH THREE BURN SCARS, BOWLS DRESS

349
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:04,960
MOTHER OF DU MINGLIANG IN ROOM 1706
SHOEMAKER MR. LU

350
00:24:05,040 --> 00:24:07,320
SONG QINGSONG LIVED IN 1703
OFTEN BROUGHT BACK DIFFERENT GIRLS

351
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:09,800
RAN FANGXU'S PATH

352
00:24:36,040 --> 00:24:36,880
Hello?

353
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:39,520
Where are you?
The case briefing is about to start.

354
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:41,240
- <i>I can't make it back today.</i>
- <i>What?</i>

355
00:24:41,320 --> 00:24:43,160
The case report,
I sent it to Captain Qu last night.

356
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:45,320
Director Zou wants to praise
you by name at the briefing.

357
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:48,000
- How can you not be there?
- I'm dealing with something urgent.

358
00:24:48,080 --> 00:24:49,520
I'll ask Captain Zhao
to file my leave request later.

359
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:51,800
What are you busy with? Why so urgent?

360
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:55,840
Captain Ran's last wish.

361
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:27,760
Qiao. Come on.

362
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:28,760
Have a seat inside.

363
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:40,560
Uncle He.

364
00:25:41,720 --> 00:25:42,840
I need to apologize to you.

365
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:47,640
About the demolition,
I did my best to persuade the boss.

366
00:25:47,720 --> 00:25:49,520
But he still sided with Qian Dajun.

367
00:25:49,600 --> 00:25:52,840
He's already given him
full control of the demolition.

368
00:25:52,920 --> 00:25:56,400
Yuanlongli
will likely be demolished early.

369
00:25:56,480 --> 00:25:57,560
I figured.

370
00:25:58,080 --> 00:26:00,040
They started playing dirty last night.

371
00:26:05,680 --> 00:26:06,520
I'm sorry, Uncle He.

372
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:08,600
Why are you apologizing?

373
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:09,680
It's not your fault.

374
00:26:10,840 --> 00:26:12,800
It's actually better that you're not
caught in the middle.

375
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:15,480
Uncle He, please don't do anything rash.

376
00:26:15,560 --> 00:26:18,000
Qian Dajun might do something even worse.

377
00:26:18,080 --> 00:26:19,080
- Who knows what he'll do?
- Let him!

378
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:20,880
I dare him to try!

379
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:22,640
Uncle He.

380
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:24,840
If anything happens to you,

381
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:27,520
Ran won't be at peace in the afterlife.

382
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:29,920
To see the Eye of the Vortex,

383
00:26:30,440 --> 00:26:32,800
you must become part
of the Eye of the Vortex.

384
00:26:35,360 --> 00:26:37,040
Those were Ran's words.

385
00:26:37,120 --> 00:26:38,360
None of you understood him.

386
00:26:39,480 --> 00:26:41,320
Only by making up for his regrets

387
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:43,040
can he find peace.

388
00:26:50,440 --> 00:26:51,280
Uncle He.

389
00:26:51,360 --> 00:26:56,720
Ran gave this to me
just before New Year in 2003.

390
00:26:56,800 --> 00:26:59,960
I don't know
if it can help with what you're doing.

391
00:27:01,960 --> 00:27:03,440
Ran gave you this?

392
00:27:03,520 --> 00:27:04,360
What is it?

393
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:08,360
I promised Ran

394
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:10,680
I'd only open it

395
00:27:11,920 --> 00:27:12,960
when he said I could.

396
00:27:13,560 --> 00:27:16,680
But he never got to say it.

397
00:27:21,120 --> 00:27:22,720
SEAL

398
00:27:37,680 --> 00:27:39,360
LIANGLIANG COMPUTER SUPPLIES

399
00:27:43,040 --> 00:27:45,040
What are you doing? Building a bunker?

400
00:27:45,120 --> 00:27:47,920
Uncle He, the surface world has fallen.

401
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:49,720
Next is our underground world.

402
00:27:49,800 --> 00:27:51,480
I have to arm myself.

403
00:27:52,880 --> 00:27:54,120
Open up and let me in first.

404
00:27:54,200 --> 00:27:55,120
Right.

405
00:28:07,960 --> 00:28:11,120
Uncle He, this drive was formatted.

406
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:13,560
Everything inside was wiped.
It's all gone.

407
00:28:15,760 --> 00:28:16,680
What do we do?

408
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:18,400
Can you recover it?

409
00:28:18,480 --> 00:28:20,720
This belonged to Officer Ran.
It's important.

410
00:28:21,280 --> 00:28:22,320
Three minutes.

411
00:28:27,520 --> 00:28:29,040
‪TOOLS, OPEN DISK

412
00:28:34,200 --> 00:28:35,040
Almost done.

413
00:28:36,680 --> 00:28:41,240
BOWLS INDUSTRIAL CO., LTD.

414
00:28:44,400 --> 00:28:46,680
You must be Officer He, right?

415
00:28:47,240 --> 00:28:48,480
- Hello.
- Hello.

416
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:51,840
BOWLS INDUSTRIAL CO., LTD.

417
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:55,200
WEIYANG STORE

418
00:28:55,280 --> 00:28:56,720
1996 to 2005.

419
00:28:57,720 --> 00:28:59,880
The Weiyang store's sales records
are all here.

420
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:04,280
Officer He, take your time.

421
00:29:04,360 --> 00:29:05,640
I'll make you some tea.

422
00:29:05,720 --> 00:29:07,160
- Thank you.
- No problem.

423
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:13,560
SALES LOG

424
00:29:15,640 --> 00:29:19,280
SUBJECT SEARCH: SUN ZHENGYONG

425
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:24,160
DRY CLEANING GIFTCARD REFUND
FOR A SAME DRESS

426
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:32,840
SUBJECT SEARCH: XU MENG

427
00:29:32,920 --> 00:29:34,360
DRY CLEANING LOG
CLIENT: XU MENG, BUYER: YAO XINCHENG

428
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:35,280
Found it.

429
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:39,240
According to the dry-cleaning record,
the buyer linked to this dress

430
00:29:39,320 --> 00:29:40,520
is Yao Xingcheng.

431
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:44,360
He bought it on December 29, 1996,
at our store.

432
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:46,600
Yao Xingcheng?

433
00:29:46,680 --> 00:29:47,600
BUYER YAO XINCHENG

434
00:29:47,680 --> 00:29:50,760
RETURN REASON: OTHER REASONS

435
00:29:50,840 --> 00:29:52,400
RETURN DATE: 1997/7/2

436
00:29:52,480 --> 00:29:53,600
That's strange.

437
00:29:54,280 --> 00:29:55,120
What is it?

438
00:29:55,720 --> 00:30:00,280
This Yao Xingcheng's information
only appears in the return record.

439
00:30:00,360 --> 00:30:03,040
His name isn't in the purchase record.

440
00:30:03,640 --> 00:30:07,520
He bought the dress
on December 29 in store.

441
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:09,760
It was returned on July 2.

442
00:30:10,360 --> 00:30:11,960
The note says, "new returned for old".

443
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:14,920
What does that mean?

444
00:30:15,840 --> 00:30:18,000
One moment. I'll ask the manager.

445
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:27,880
Hello, Officer.

446
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:29,640
I wrote that note.

447
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:31,720
Back then, this customer
came back after over six months

448
00:30:31,800 --> 00:30:33,240
to make the return.

449
00:30:33,320 --> 00:30:35,600
But the tags and packaging
were all intact.

450
00:30:35,680 --> 00:30:37,800
So the counter canceled the order.

451
00:30:38,560 --> 00:30:40,360
What did the person
who returned it look like?

452
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:41,840
Do you remember?

453
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:42,960
I didn't handle the return.

454
00:30:43,040 --> 00:30:46,040
I only found the order while making
that day's report.

455
00:30:46,120 --> 00:30:49,240
This dress had its
button supplier changed in 1997.

456
00:30:49,320 --> 00:30:52,400
This customer bought the old version,
but returned the new one.

457
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:54,080
I found it strange too.

458
00:30:54,160 --> 00:30:57,000
That's why I wrote that note.

459
00:30:58,560 --> 00:31:00,120
BOWLS FLAGSHIP STORE, SOLD BY SUSAN
COMMENT: WITH ONE DRY CLEANING GIFT CARD

460
00:31:00,800 --> 00:31:02,400
Officer.

461
00:31:02,480 --> 00:31:05,280
The returned dress wasn't bought here.

462
00:31:05,360 --> 00:31:06,640
It was bought
at the provincial flagship store.

463
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:08,800
What do you mean?

464
00:31:09,600 --> 00:31:10,880
Here's the thing.

465
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:14,880
This new dress was only distributed
on June 30, 1997.

466
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:17,400
It arrived at the provincial store
on July 1.

467
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:19,960
Our Weiyang store is farther away.
It arrived a week later.

468
00:31:20,480 --> 00:31:21,800
So you mean

469
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:25,360
on July 2, your store wasn't selling
this new style yet?

470
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:26,480
Right. Look.

471
00:31:26,560 --> 00:31:29,040
On July 2, at 10:05 a.m.,

472
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:31,520
the provincial flagship store
had a sales record

473
00:31:31,600 --> 00:31:32,440
for the same dress.

474
00:31:32,520 --> 00:31:35,000
But in this record,
there's no customer name.

475
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:37,600
The return at our store

476
00:31:38,320 --> 00:31:40,200
was at 4:20 p.m. that same day.

477
00:31:44,280 --> 00:31:45,520
Strange.

478
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:47,160
Bought it in the provincial capital
that morning,

479
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:48,680
then spent hours rushing to Weiyang,

480
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:50,160
just to return the dress.

481
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:51,760
Why go through all that?

482
00:31:57,800 --> 00:31:59,480
This return is strange.

483
00:31:59,560 --> 00:32:01,560
Jessica. Mark it clearly.

484
00:32:01,640 --> 00:32:04,280
In case the customer asks later,
we'll have an explanation.

485
00:32:04,360 --> 00:32:05,640
Yes, Manager.

486
00:32:10,640 --> 00:32:13,320
NOTE: NEW FOR OLD, BOUGHT IN CAPITAL
RETURNED IN WEIYANG. JESSICA

487
00:32:15,520 --> 00:32:18,560
This customer
bought it in the capital that morning,

488
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:20,000
then returned it in Weiyang
that afternoon.

489
00:32:20,080 --> 00:32:22,040
And it canceled a record
from over six months ago.

490
00:32:22,840 --> 00:32:23,760
Why?

491
00:32:26,560 --> 00:32:28,520
Maybe they wanted to use the return

492
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:30,960
to erase Yao Xingcheng's purchase record.

493
00:32:31,680 --> 00:32:35,080
Ma'am, can you help me contact
the Jessica who wrote this note?

494
00:32:35,160 --> 00:32:37,080
Jessica from the Weiyang store.

495
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:39,800
I need to check HR's computer.

496
00:32:39,880 --> 00:32:40,880
One moment.

497
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:42,640
- Thank you.
- No problem.

498
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:47,120
Right. Can I make a copy of these files?

499
00:32:47,680 --> 00:32:49,400
Sure. You can copy them yourself.

500
00:33:06,560 --> 00:33:07,520
Uncle Ran,

501
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:10,600
back then,

502
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:12,720
did you find this too?

503
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:20,680
SUBJECT SEARCH: RAN FANGXU

504
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:23,200
SEARCH

505
00:33:23,280 --> 00:33:25,280
DATE: 2003/1/29, WEIYANG FLAGSHIP
CLIENT: RAN FANGXU

506
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:28,760
SALESPERSON: JESSICA

507
00:33:30,960 --> 00:33:32,360
STORE: WEIYANG FLAGSHIP
CUSTOMER: RAN FANGXU

508
00:33:32,440 --> 00:33:33,280
<i>Thank you for your cooperation.</i>

509
00:33:34,120 --> 00:33:34,960
Of course.

510
00:33:35,040 --> 00:33:36,680
- I'll get going.
- Okay. Take care.

511
00:33:36,760 --> 00:33:37,640
See him out.

512
00:33:38,320 --> 00:33:39,480
Officer.

513
00:33:39,560 --> 00:33:40,680
New Year is coming soon.

514
00:33:40,760 --> 00:33:43,240
Would you like to see some clothes
and pick one for your family?

515
00:33:52,400 --> 00:33:53,440
Officer.

516
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:55,520
You're handsome, and you have great taste.

517
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:57,240
This just came in.
It's the Year of the Goat style.

518
00:33:57,320 --> 00:33:59,360
I can give you an extra discount.

519
00:34:10,159 --> 00:34:11,120
I recovered one file.

520
00:34:19,600 --> 00:34:20,440
Uncle He,

521
00:34:21,199 --> 00:34:23,520
why did Officer Ran save this?

522
00:34:24,440 --> 00:34:25,760
Just close it first.

523
00:34:26,639 --> 00:34:28,120
Right. Eyes off.

524
00:34:38,679 --> 00:34:39,600
He,

525
00:34:42,840 --> 00:34:45,199
this hard drive was probably found
at Wu Shanlong's home.

526
00:34:45,800 --> 00:34:47,480
By procedure, after a case closes,

527
00:34:47,560 --> 00:34:49,639
all assets go to judicial auction.

528
00:34:50,400 --> 00:34:52,000
So this hard drive was wiped.

529
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:53,600
Looks like

530
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:57,720
Ran must have bought this hard drive.

531
00:34:58,920 --> 00:35:00,200
I get it.

532
00:35:00,280 --> 00:35:02,000
After this drive was auctioned,

533
00:35:02,080 --> 00:35:05,240
if someone like me knew data recovery,

534
00:35:06,720 --> 00:35:10,160
Officer Ran was afraid the victims
would be hurt again.

535
00:35:12,320 --> 00:35:13,960
That was Ran.

536
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:17,200
He cared about everyone.

537
00:35:21,200 --> 00:35:23,320
Hello. Please wrap these two for me.

538
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:26,720
Do you want to wear it now?
I'll take the tag off.

539
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:28,560
Sure, thanks.

540
00:35:32,480 --> 00:35:35,440
OULI FASHION BOUTIQUE

541
00:35:36,040 --> 00:35:37,120
Welcome.

542
00:36:01,680 --> 00:36:03,240
Do you like this color?

543
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:08,840
I came to pick a scarf for Sir.

544
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:09,800
I didn't expect you here.

545
00:36:13,960 --> 00:36:16,480
Which one do you think
would look good on Sir?

546
00:36:18,640 --> 00:36:20,080
No need to bother.

547
00:36:20,160 --> 00:36:22,720
You and Officer He each get one. My treat.

548
00:36:23,600 --> 00:36:24,640
No.

549
00:36:24,720 --> 00:36:26,600
New Year's gift. You can't refuse.

550
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:33,320
Please wrap them up.

551
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:34,280
- Sure.
- Thanks.

552
00:36:34,360 --> 00:36:37,760
Sir, I saw your wife
helping you choose for ages.

553
00:36:37,840 --> 00:36:39,880
You two are really close. That's so sweet.

554
00:36:52,320 --> 00:36:53,640
Why did you buy two too?

555
00:36:55,200 --> 00:36:56,760
This one is for Xiaohe.

556
00:36:57,400 --> 00:36:58,800
You got Officer He a gift.

557
00:36:58,880 --> 00:37:01,320
I can't show up empty-handed
and eat for free.

558
00:37:16,280 --> 00:37:18,840
You try it on.

559
00:37:20,080 --> 00:37:21,000
For me?

560
00:37:24,080 --> 00:37:26,440
This, how much was it?

561
00:37:26,520 --> 00:37:28,120
Wool is expensive.

562
00:37:29,720 --> 00:37:31,080
NATIONAL RETAIL PRICE: 1,888 YUAN

563
00:37:31,160 --> 00:37:32,640
This, this is too expensive.

564
00:37:32,720 --> 00:37:34,160
You should return it.

565
00:37:35,040 --> 00:37:35,920
Don't look at the tag price.

566
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:38,240
I got an extra discount.
It wasn't expensive.

567
00:37:40,800 --> 00:37:41,680
This is a New Year's gift too.

568
00:37:41,760 --> 00:37:42,760
You can't refuse.

569
00:37:47,920 --> 00:37:51,560
You don’t make much every month,
and you still spend like this.

570
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:53,920
You really don’t know
how to manage your money.

571
00:38:08,400 --> 00:38:10,720
I reached Jessica
from the Weiyang store in 2003.

572
00:38:10,800 --> 00:38:13,000
It matches the clues
Uncle Ran found back then.

573
00:38:14,160 --> 00:38:16,360
We finally caught up with Uncle Ran.

574
00:38:16,440 --> 00:38:19,240
Great. This Yao Xingcheng

575
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:21,760
is the key to cracking
the Yuanlongli June 30th case.

576
00:38:21,840 --> 00:38:24,360
The Bowls dress at Xu Meng's home
was bought by him.

577
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:26,320
<i>He didn't want anyone to find out.</i>

578
00:38:26,840 --> 00:38:30,040
<i>So, he used a return</i>
<i>to erase the purchase record.</i>

579
00:38:30,640 --> 00:38:34,560
Also, the man
who went to Mr. Lu to turn red heels

580
00:38:34,640 --> 00:38:36,400
was most likely him too.

581
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:37,640
<i>Here's the plan.</i>

582
00:38:37,720 --> 00:38:40,440
<i>We keep working both ends.</i>
<i>Once you're back in Weiyang,</i>

583
00:38:40,520 --> 00:38:41,920
go to the bureau first.

584
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:43,360
Search the internal network.

585
00:38:43,440 --> 00:38:45,880
<i>I'll contact Xu Meng's family now.</i>

586
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:49,160
We'll try to find this Yao Xingcheng
as soon as possible.

587
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:51,240
- Okay.
- <i>Talk later.</i>

588
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:56,880
Auntie Xu.

589
00:38:57,680 --> 00:38:58,920
Xu.

590
00:39:00,560 --> 00:39:01,920
NEW YORK BLOCK

591
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:05,640
Both corners, put signal blockers on them.

592
00:39:05,720 --> 00:39:08,520
Not one call or text gets out
of this building!

593
00:39:08,600 --> 00:39:10,720
- Got it!
- Okay!

594
00:39:15,160 --> 00:39:16,120
Mr. Qian,

595
00:39:16,200 --> 00:39:19,520
what if the residents run out
and call the police?

596
00:39:20,680 --> 00:39:21,520
Are you stupid?

597
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:25,240
Cut it off for half an hour,
then turn it back on.

598
00:39:25,320 --> 00:39:28,040
Turn it on, then cut it off.
Cut it off, then turn it on.

599
00:39:28,120 --> 00:39:28,960
AUNTIE XU

600
00:39:29,040 --> 00:39:30,160
Auntie Xu.

601
00:39:39,720 --> 00:39:42,240
NO SERVICE

602
00:39:45,720 --> 00:39:46,840
Qian Dajun!

603
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:48,800
You shameless piece of trash!

604
00:40:02,480 --> 00:40:03,400
Officer He.

605
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:05,240
Heading out?

606
00:40:05,320 --> 00:40:06,480
Qian Dajun.

607
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:11,000
What goes around comes around.

608
00:40:11,800 --> 00:40:14,240
It’s just a matter of time.

609
00:40:24,040 --> 00:40:24,920
See that?

610
00:40:25,440 --> 00:40:28,400
Even that stubborn old man
can't take it anymore.

611
00:40:29,240 --> 00:40:31,240
Those old fools upstairs,

612
00:40:31,320 --> 00:40:33,520
all they’ve got is a big mouth.

613
00:40:33,600 --> 00:40:35,240
Qian Dajun!

614
00:40:35,320 --> 00:40:36,640
You rotten punk!

615
00:40:36,720 --> 00:40:37,960
I'll end you!

616
00:40:38,480 --> 00:40:40,160
Underground garage…

617
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:45,360
The underground garage
still has a few holdouts.

618
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:47,880
Especially that Du Mingliang.

619
00:40:48,480 --> 00:40:50,400
Even that little punk dares to act up.

620
00:40:50,480 --> 00:40:51,840
Then we start with him.

621
00:40:52,680 --> 00:40:54,480
Make an example of him.

622
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:05,400
BLESSING

623
00:41:23,800 --> 00:41:27,360
BLESSING, GOOD FORTUNE

624
00:41:40,640 --> 00:41:41,760
Auntie Xu.

625
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:44,920
Who is it?

626
00:41:50,600 --> 00:41:52,120
It's me, Auntie Xu.

627
00:41:58,680 --> 00:41:59,880
Officer He?

628
00:42:02,520 --> 00:42:04,960
Officer He, you've gotten old.

629
00:42:05,040 --> 00:42:07,400
Come on, have a seat.
I'll get you some water.

630
00:42:07,480 --> 00:42:08,440
No need.

631
00:42:08,960 --> 00:42:10,440
These are for you.

632
00:42:11,080 --> 00:42:13,000
Thank you.

633
00:42:13,080 --> 00:42:15,640
I'm here to ask about something.

634
00:42:16,400 --> 00:42:19,480
Back then, did Xu Meng and Xu Zhihong

635
00:42:19,560 --> 00:42:23,720
know someone named Yao Xingcheng?

636
00:42:24,240 --> 00:42:25,680
Yao Xingcheng?

637
00:42:27,120 --> 00:42:29,520
Yao Xingcheng.

638
00:42:30,440 --> 00:42:31,280
Yao…

639
00:42:32,920 --> 00:42:35,560
I remember now. I remember.

640
00:42:35,640 --> 00:42:39,400
One year, around New Year,

641
00:42:39,480 --> 00:42:41,360
a young man came by.

642
00:42:41,440 --> 00:42:44,400
He said he was a police officer too.

643
00:42:44,480 --> 00:42:49,120
He asked me about Yao Xingcheng.

644
00:42:49,200 --> 00:42:53,520
But I had never heard that name.

645
00:42:55,200 --> 00:42:59,480
That young man was not only handsome,
but also kind.

646
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:03,360
When he left, he insisted
on giving me a red envelope.

647
00:43:03,440 --> 00:43:07,440
Officer He, how has he been?

648
00:43:08,400 --> 00:43:09,800
Is he married?

649
00:43:09,880 --> 00:43:11,680
Does he have kids?
